{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀνταπό-δοσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>giving back in turn,</b> opposed to ἀποδοχή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.81\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>rendering, requiting, repayment,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1133a3, 1163a11, +others; χάριτος 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Μονόστιχοι - Fragmenta Comicorum Graecorum” 330, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.100; τῶν εὐεργεσιῶν 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Pietate - Herkulanische Studien” 14\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>retribution,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Isa.61.2, 63.4, +others\">LXX</a>]; <b>reprisals,</b> γίγνεται ἀ. ἔκ τινος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.30.6\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>reward,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Psa.18(19).11, NT.Col.3.24. \">LXX+NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>turning back, opposite direction</b> or <b>course,</b> of a current, ἀ. ποιεῖσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.43.5, etc., compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.136b. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>responsive sound,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Audibilibus” 803a31. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>alternation,</b> e.g. of action and reaction, περιόδων πρὸς ἀλλήλας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 1.12\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>reaction,</b> probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 2p.48U., compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Ventis” 10. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> Rhet., <b>parallelism</b> or <b>opposition of clauses</b> in a periodic sentence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 23, compare 250\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; in a simile, <b>correspondence with</b> the object of comparison, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Quintilianus Rhetor Latinus “Inst.” 8.3.77. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.b</b></Level4> Grammars, <b>correlativity</b> of words such as τοιοῦτος, οἷος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 54.1. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.c</b></Level4> <b>answering clause,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ ἰδεῶν” 1.11, 2.1; see l. in 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 20.6. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>capping verses,</b> as a subject of competition, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Michel” 913 (from Teos).\">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G0469","accentedUnicode":"ἀνταπόδοσις","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0467","matchingForm":"ἀνταποδίδωμι","stepTransliteration":"antapodidōmi","gloss":"to repay","_zh_tw_Gloss":"必報應","_es_Gloss":"pagar","_zh_Gloss":"必报应"},{"strongNumber":"G0468","matchingForm":"ἀνταπόδομα","stepTransliteration":"antapodoma","gloss":"repayment","_zh_tw_Gloss":"報答","_es_Gloss":"recompensa","_zh_Gloss":"报答"},{"strongNumber":"G0473","matchingForm":"ἀντί","stepTransliteration":"anti","gloss":"for","_zh_tw_Gloss":"還, 因, 作, 為","_es_Gloss":"por","_zh_Gloss":"还, 因, 作, 为"},{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G0591","matchingForm":"ἀποδίδωμι","stepTransliteration":"apodidōmi","gloss":"to pay","_zh_tw_Gloss":"還清","_es_Gloss":"pagar","_zh_Gloss":"还清"},{"strongNumber":"G1394","matchingForm":"δόσις","stepTransliteration":"dosis","gloss":"gift","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恩賜","_es_Gloss":"regalo ","_zh_Gloss":"恩赐"}],"shortDef":"